name: Jacobine Casuarius
description:
Fig 01


Jacobine Casuarius is an Osteichthy Molluscave creature from Caleuche, an exoplanet located 124 light years away from Earth. 
Jacobine lives both in gas clouds of Fluorine as in seas of Osmium, and it may reach speeds of 210km/h swimming and 320km/h flying. 
Its size varies from 0.6m to 2.2m high as an adult, and it sleeps for 12 minutes a day in his shell-like home. 
The species has 3 kinds of genres, it may be excessively proud and it´s IQ it´s thought to be 4 times higher than the average human.
